items.subject: 9'-0" 2X6 Interior Wood Framed Wall @ 16" OC
items.description:
Wood framed wall systems act as the skeleton to a building or structure providing enclosure and support to distribute live, dead, and other structural loads across the building. Common components include headers, top/bottom plates, and studs that are to be spaced apart depending on the application or requirements determined by the engineer. 

1build assemblies are built using common assumptions for materials, sizes, and normal operation conditions. [Please ensure this assembly satisfies your project's contract requirements].

1build assemblies include only items displayed above. They can be edited and customized to fit your specific use case

items.subject: Dump Fee for Misc. Brush (Trees, Brush, Wood)
items.description: Pricing serves as a project allowance for the disposal of debris at local facility, excluding labor costs, gas, or additional allowances for driving to and from job site. This pricing should be used for allowance purposes only and is not attached to a live price source.

items.subject: 12K 55' Shooting Boom Forklift
items.description:
A 12K 55' Shooting Boom Forklift is commonly used to lift and move heavy objects. It is made up of a large metal frame with a long arm that has a large basket or platform on the end. The arm is operated by a hydraulic system, and the basket can be raised or lowered using a control lever.

Pricing includes bare rental, basic maintenance owed by supplier, and (1) delivery/pickup within a 100 mile radius of a supplier.

Pricing excludes operator costs, fuel, taxes, additional attachments, maintenance due to damage, damage waiver costs, and similar fees.

items.subject: Carpenter
items.description:
Job Description: Construct, erect, install, or repair structures and fixtures made of wood, such as concrete forms; building frameworks, including partitions, joists, studding, and rafters; and wood stairways, window and door frames, and hardwood floors.  May also install cabinets, siding, drywall and batt or roll insulation. Includes brattice builders who build doors or brattices (ventilation walls or partitions) in underground passageways

Pricing reflects an average base hourly rate for (1) crew member based on data collected from external labor sources like US Bureau of Labor Statistics, ZipRecruiter, and Indeed.com. 

Pricing excludes any fringe benefits, taxes, deductions, overhead costs, insurance costs, markups, or other burden costs which should be added by the user.
